
1. Download Power BI Desktop:

   Go to the official Power BI website: [https://powerbi.microsoft.com/desktop](https://powerbi.microsoft.com/desktop).

•	Click the "Download free" button to start the download.

2. Installation:

•	Locate the downloaded installer file (usually named something like "PBIDesktopSetup.exe").

•	Double-click the installer file to begin the installation.

3. Setup Wizard:

•	The Power BI Desktop Setup Wizard will open.

4. Accept License Terms:

•	Review the license terms, and if you agree, select the "I accept the terms in the License Agreement" checkbox.

•	Click the "Install" button to proceed.

5. Installation Progress:

•	    The installer will now copy files and install Power BI Desktop on your computer. This process may take a few minutes.

6. Completion:

•	   Once the installation is complete, you'll see a message confirming the successful installation of Power BI Desktop.

7. Launch Power BI Desktop:

•	   You can choose to launch Power BI Desktop immediately by keeping the "Launch Power BI Desktop" option checked.

•	   Click the "Finish" button to complete the installation.

8. Starting Power BI Desktop:

•	   After installation, you can start Power BI Desktop by clicking its icon on your desktop or from the Windows Start menu.

